A simple messaging system for Meshtastic that uses the TEXTMSG serial
function to send selected messages triggered by the received messages. 
There is also a dashboard page for sending and receiving messages.

All messages are received and sent to the first (primary) Meshtastic channel, 
so if you want to use this application in a private group, that group MUST be 
the FIRST channel on the Meshtastic node handling messaging. See publisjhed 
docs for more info.

You'll find more setup details at: https://github.com/linker3000/MeshBop

Feel free to suggest improvements or changes. It will be especially helpful
to receive flows to use this app with other news and weather services.

Notes:

Read all these notes carefully. before changing anything.

The accuracy and results of these flows depends on your setup work and third party code.
This app is supplied 'as is'. Use at your own risk. No responsibility is accepted for 
consequential loss or errors. Feedback is welcome at the address above or the Issues
tab at the GitHub project page.

As of September 2025, there is a bug in the Meshtastic node firmware, and TEXTMSG
mode (used by this code) may transmit a spurious character when the node is powered
on or off. This has been reported and is nothing to do with this app.

*** Some features in this app are disabled by default. See the notes below. ***

*** Some pages have further notes and comments in the top left corner of their tab  ***

************************************************************************************
When testing, disable the Async out node on this tab and save
your change so that you don't send out test messages. You can see what's being
generated in the debug window on that tab.
Do pre-live testing in a secondary (private) channel.
Remember to re-enable the node when you're ready to rock.

The Async out node may already be disabled when you install these flows - do check.

Some flows have rate limiting nodes, please respect the mesh and don't do 
anything that might flood it with messages. If in doubt, disable the 
Async out node on this tab and reload Node-RED before testing.

Some flows have inject inputs for testing. If any of the functionality (such
as message triggering) is changed, these may need to be changed too.
************************************************************************************
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Set global variables below. Some variables may be 'for future use'.

>> If you want emails sent (eg: Severe weather warnings):

* Configure your email details address below.
* Configure, enable (if disabled) and test the Email node on this tab.
* By default, the severe weather warnings are only sent to email. Modify the 
*   link-outs on that page when you are good to send to the Mesh too.

>> Things you must do here and on other tabs:

* Set the async port parameters for the input and output nodes. These must match those
  set on your Meshtastic node in its radio configuration.

If running on a Linux system, and your async in and out nodes don't work 
or don't show as 'connected', you may need to add the account running Node-RED
to the 'dialout' group or equivalent for your distribution. This is well-documented -
try a Web search for 'linux dialout serial'.

* The weather info comes from Open-Meteo and should work if the Lat and Long
  are set below to the right location, otherwise the fallback is central London.

* Set up and enable the Severe Weather flow (Optional - see its tab for more notes)
    By default, the severe weather warnings are picked up from the UK Met Office and
    Open-Meteo (thunderstorms and high winds). You might wish to change this.

* Check or set your message trigger texts in the "Parse Rx message" function
    on this tab.

* Modify your Help messages to match your trigger texts.

*/

// SET THESE...

// The trigger pattern for your messages - recommended to be a slash followed
// by your pattern, for example, mine is /l3k, so to trigger the news
//response, someone sends /l3kn etc..
global.set('basePattern', '/l3k');

// The pattern that is used to send a help/info message
// set to '' if you don't have one. This should match how the function 
// block on this tab is set to trigger for this message.  
global.set('helpMsg','/l3k?');

// Fixed IP address of this server (not actually used yet if this message is here)
global.set ('myIP','0.0.0.0');

// Set your location (static text) - used in some messages. 
// If not set, 'London' will be used'
global.set('location', '');

// Set your Region - a more generalised location.
// If not set, 'London' will be used'
global.set('region', '');

//Set this for Astro and weather. 
// If not set Central London will be used
global.set('latitude', '');   
global.set('longitude', '');  
global.set('height', 10.0);  // Elevation above MSL in meters

//For timezone:
global.set('locale','en-GB');

//Set your email addresses for weather alerts (if email is enabled):
global.set('emailTo', '')
global.set('emailFrom', '')

// Also set your email account details (user name and password etc.)
// in the email node on this tab, and the email node may 
// need to be enabled.

// Don't change these please!
global.set('version','MeshBop V0.04 beta.');
global.set('info','MeshBop is a Meshtastic messaging system written in Node-RED. https://github.com/linker3000/MeshBop');

msg.payload = true;
return msg;

let str = msg.payload;

// Remove any leading or trailing spaces in the received message.
str = str.trim();

// Remove any non-ASCII characters in the middle of the string
str = str.replace(/[^\x20-\x7E]/g, '');  // Keeps printable ASCII characters (0x20 to 0x7E)

if (str == '') return null;

msg.payload = str;
return msg;

let payloadLength = (typeof msg.payload === 'string') ? msg.payload.length : 0;

msg.payload = msg.payload + " (" + payloadLength + ")";
node.warn (msg.payload)
return null;

// Parses the received message and decides what to do with it.
// This is all done with Regex (sorry!), but is not too hard
// to work out and test if you check out the default conditions below.
// You can keep these defaults, change them or add your own.
//
// ** If you add a new test, remember to go to the setup tab here and
// add another output for it.
//
// Always test with the Tx node disabled + in a private channel 
// before you 'go live'. 

// Check for null message first - if so, do nothing.
if (!msg || msg.payload === null || msg.payload === undefined) {
    return null;
}

// Get the trigger prefix being looked for. Just in case it's unset
// in the global parameters you can put a fallback here.
// Once defined, the message triggers all start with the prefix
// string so, for example, we can have a trigger on /l3kz to get 
// a random inspirational (or otherwise!) Zen message.
//
// To help with debugging, info about the chosen output is 
// sent to output 1, which has a debug node connected to it. 

// Changing the l3k here will change the default message trigger check.
// It can be left 'as is' if the basePattern global variable is set
// properly in the setup function block on the first tab because
// that will override the l3k here.
let basePattern = global.get("basePattern") || "/l3k";
node.warn(basePattern);

// Convert payload to string and strip sender ID
let content = String(msg.payload || "").replace(/^[^:]+:\s*/, "");

// Define the regex patterns with dynamic base and descriptions
const patterns = [
    {regex: new RegExp(basePattern + "w$"), desc: "w pattern"},                    // Output 2
    {regex: new RegExp(basePattern + "n(,\\d+(,u)?)?$"), desc: "n pattern"},       // Output 3  
    {regex: new RegExp(basePattern + "\\?$"), desc: "? pattern"},                  // Output 4
    {regex: new RegExp(basePattern + "t$"), desc: "t pattern"},                    // Output 5
    {regex: new RegExp(basePattern + "z$"), desc: "z Zen message"},                // Output 6
    {regex: new RegExp("(test|testing)$"), desc: "test pattern"},                  // Output 7
    {regex: new RegExp("ping$"), desc: "ping pattern"},                            // Output 8
    {regex: new RegExp(basePattern + "i$"), desc: "i pattern"},                    // Output 9

];

// Test each pattern against the stripped message
for (let i = 0; i < patterns.length; i++) {
    if (patterns[i].regex.test(content)) {
        // Create debug message for first output
        let debugMsg = {
            payload: `Output ${i + 2} selected: "${content}" matched ${patterns[i].desc} (${patterns[i].regex.source})`
        };

        // Create array of 8 null outputs (1 debug + 7 original)
        let outputs = new Array(8).fill(null);
        outputs[0] = debugMsg;           // Debug output
        outputs[i + 1] = msg;           // Original message to matching output
        return outputs;
    }
}

// No match found - send debug message
let noMatchMsg = {payload: `No match found for: "${content}"`};
let outputs = new Array(8).fill(null);
outputs[0] = noMatchMsg;
return outputs;

if (global.get('version') && global.get('helpMsg')) {
    msg.payload = global.get('version') + ' Send "' + global.get('helpMsg') + '" for menu.';
    return msg;
} else {
    return null; // Don't send anything if either value is missing or empty
}

let message = msg.payload;

// Split the message at each newline (\r) character
let sections = message.split('\r');

// Regular expression to match and remove non-ASCII characters
let asciiOnlyRegex = /[^\x20-\x7E]/g;

// Max length for each segment
const MAX_LENGTH = 198;

function sendSection(i) {
    if (i < sections.length) {
        // Clean the section: remove non-ASCII characters
        let cleanedSection = sections[i].replace(asciiOnlyRegex, '');

        // Skip sending empty sections
        if (cleanedSection === '') {
            sendSection(i + 1);
            return;
        }

        // Break the cleaned section into chunks of MAX_LENGTH
        for (let start = 0; start < cleanedSection.length; start += MAX_LENGTH) {
            let chunk = cleanedSection.substring(start, start + MAX_LENGTH);

            // Add a newline (\r) only if this is the final chunk
            // of this section *and* it is not the last overall section
            if (start + MAX_LENGTH >= cleanedSection.length && i < sections.length - 1) {
                chunk += '\r';
            }

            let newMsg = { ...msg };
            newMsg.payload = chunk;
            node.send(newMsg);
        }

        // Process the next section
        sendSection(i + 1);
    }
}

// Start processing
sendSection(0);

// Prevent the original message from being sent
return null;

let parts = msg.payload.split(":");
let location = global.get('location') || 'London';
let currentTime = new Date().toLocaleTimeString(global.get('locale') || 'en-GB', { hour12: false });

msg.payload = `Hello ${parts[0].trim()}. ${parts[1].trim().charAt(0).toUpperCase() 
  + parts[1].trim().slice(1).toLowerCase()
    } received in ${location} at ${currentTime}` + ' (local).';

return msg;

// Ensure the data is available in msg (sunRise and sunSet)
let sunrise = msg.sunRise;
let sunset = msg.sunSet;

// Truncate sunrise and sunset to just HH:MM (remove the seconds)
sunrise = sunrise.substring(0, 5);  // Extracts the first 5 characters (HH:MM)
sunset = sunset.substring(0, 5);    // Same for sunset

// Get the current local time in 24-hour format, truncating to HH:MM (no seconds)
let currentTime = new Date().toLocaleTimeString(global.get('locale') || 'en-GB', {
    hour12: false,
    hour: '2-digit',
    minute: '2-digit'
});

// Get the current UTC time in 24-hour format, truncating to HH:MM (no seconds)
let utcTime = new Date().toUTCString().split(' ')[4].substring(0, 5);  // Truncate to HH:MM

// Construct the message
msg.payload = (global.get('location') || 'London') +
    ': Local time ' + currentTime +
    ' (' + utcTime + ' UTC)' +
    '. Sunrise: ' + sunrise +
    ', Sunset: ' + sunset + ' (local times).';

return msg;

// Retrieve global variables to be used in the call to astrodata
msg.lat = global.get('latitude') || 51.5074;
msg.lon = global.get('longitude') || -0.1278;
msg.height = global.get('height') || 10;

return msg;

// Get coordinates from global context, fallback to centre of London
let lat = global.get('latitude') || 51.5074;
let lon = global.get('longitude') || -0.1278;

// Set the URL with additional parameters
msg.url = `https://api.open-meteo.com/v1/forecast?latitude=${lat}&longitude=${lon}&current=temperature_2m,apparent_temperature,weather_code,wind_speed_10m,wind_direction_10m,pressure_msl&timezone=Europe/London`;
return msg;

// Debug: Check what we're receiving
node.warn("Full message: " + JSON.stringify(msg));
node.warn("Payload type: " + typeof msg.payload);
node.warn("Payload: " + JSON.stringify(msg.payload));

// Handle different response formats
var weatherData;
if (typeof msg.payload === "string") {
    // If it's a string, parse it as JSON
    try {
        weatherData = JSON.parse(msg.payload);
    } catch (e) {
        node.error("Failed to parse JSON: " + e.message);
        return null;
    }
} else if (typeof msg.payload === "object") {
    // If it's already an object, use it directly
    weatherData = msg.payload;
} else {
    node.error("Unexpected payload type: " + typeof msg.payload);
    return null;
}

// Check if we have the expected structure
if (!weatherData || !weatherData.current) {
    node.error("Invalid payload structure. Expected current weather data");
    node.error("Available keys: " + Object.keys(weatherData || {}));
    return null;
}

var airPressure = weatherData.current.pressure_msl;
var windAngle = weatherData.current.wind_direction_10m;
var windCompass = {};
var windSpeed = {};
var weatherDescription = {};
var airTemperature = {};
var feelsLikeTemp = {};
var fullWeatherString = {};
var msgPressure = {};
var weatherCodeOutput = {};

var compassDirections = ["North", "North-East", "East", "South-East", "South", "South-West", "West", "North-West"];

var weatherDescriptions = {
    0: "Clear sky",
    1: "Mainly clear",
    2: "Partly cloudy",
    3: "Overcast",
    45: "Fog",
    48: "Depositing rime fog",
    51: "Light drizzle",
    53: "Moderate drizzle",
    55: "Dense drizzle",
    61: "Slight rain",
    63: "Moderate rain",
    65: "Heavy rain",
    71: "Slight snow",
    73: "Moderate snow",
    75: "Heavy snow",
    95: "Thunderstorm"
};

// Calculate direction and store in object
var windDirectionText = compassDirections[Math.round(((windAngle %= 360) < 0 ? windAngle + 360 : windAngle) / 45) % 8];
windCompass = { payload: windDirectionText };

// Wind speed in mph, rounded to nearest 0.5
windSpeed = {
    payload: Math.round(weatherData.current.wind_speed_10m * 0.621371 * 2) / 2
};

msgPressure.payload = airPressure;
airTemperature.payload = weatherData.current.temperature_2m.toFixed(1) + "C";

// Handle apparent temperature
feelsLikeTemp.payload = weatherData.current.apparent_temperature ?
    weatherData.current.apparent_temperature.toFixed(1) + "C" :
    airTemperature.payload;

// Get weather description from code
var weatherCode = weatherData.current.weather_code;
weatherDescription.payload = weatherDescriptions[weatherCode] || ("Weather code " + weatherCode);

// Weather code as separate output
weatherCodeOutput.payload = weatherCode;

// Assemble final string
var locationName = global.get("location") || "London";
fullWeatherString.payload = locationName + ": " +
    weatherDescription.payload +
    ". Temp: " + airTemperature.payload +
    ". Feels like: " + feelsLikeTemp.payload +
    ". Wind: " + windSpeed.payload + "mph " + windCompass.payload +
    ". Pressure: " + msgPressure.payload + "mb";

return [windCompass, windSpeed, weatherDescription, msgPressure, airTemperature, feelsLikeTemp, weatherCodeOutput,fullWeatherString];

const feed = msg.payload;

// Check for a valid RSS structure with at least one item
if (
    !feed.rss ||
    !Array.isArray(feed.rss.channel) ||
    feed.rss.channel.length === 0 ||
    !Array.isArray(feed.rss.channel[0].item) ||
    feed.rss.channel[0].item.length === 0
) {
    return null; // No warnings — return no output
}

// Extract the first warning item
const firstItem = feed.rss.channel[0].item[0];

// Extract and trim the description
let description = firstItem.description?.[0]?.trim() || "";
description = description.substring(0, 198);

// Extract the URL from the guid field
const url = firstItem.guid?.[0]?._ || "";

// Assign to message fields
msg.payload = description;
msg.message = description;
msg.url = url;

return msg;

// Get the long URL from msg.payload
let longUrl = msg.url;

// Check if the long URL is valid
if (!longUrl || typeof longUrl !== 'string') {
    node.error("Invalid URL", msg);
    return null;  // Exit the function if the URL is invalid
}

// Check if the URL contains a '?'
let questionMarkIndex = longUrl.indexOf('?');

// If it contains a '?', remove everything after it, including the '?' itself
if (questionMarkIndex !== -1) {
    longUrl = longUrl.substring(0, questionMarkIndex);  // Keep the part before '?'
}

// Prepare the URL for TinyURL
let tinyUrlApi = `https://tinyurl.com/api-create.php?url=${encodeURIComponent(longUrl)}`;

// Set the HTTP request configuration
msg.url = tinyUrlApi;  // TinyURL API endpoint

return msg;

let message = msg.message || "";
let tinyurl = msg.payload || "";

let combined = message + " " + tinyurl;

if (combined.length > 198) {
    // Reserve space for two dots and the space before tinyurl
    let maxMessageLength = 198 - (tinyurl.length + 1 + 2); // +1 for space, +2 for ".."

    // Truncate message and add ".."
    message = message.substring(0, maxMessageLength).trim() + "..";

    combined = message + " " + tinyurl;
}

msg.payload = combined;
msg.topic = "MeshBop: SEVERE WEATHER WARNING"
return msg;

// Get coordinates from global context, fallback to centre of London
let lat = global.get('latitude') || 51.5074;
let lon = global.get('longitude') || -0.1278;

// Get relevant weather info from call to Open-Meteo
msg.url = `https://api.open-meteo.com/v1/forecast?latitude=${lat}&longitude=${lon}&current=weather_code,wind_speed_10m&timezone=Europe/London`;

return msg;

// Handle different response formats from HTTP request
var weatherData;
if (typeof msg.payload === "string") {
    try {
        weatherData = JSON.parse(msg.payload);
    } catch (e) {
        node.error("Failed to parse JSON: " + e.message);
        return null;
    }
} else if (typeof msg.payload === "object") {
    weatherData = msg.payload;
} else {
    node.error("Unexpected payload type: " + typeof msg.payload);
    return null;
}

// Check if we have the expected structure
if (!weatherData || !weatherData.current) {
    node.error("Invalid payload structure. Expected current weather data");
    return null;
}

// Extract weather data
var weatherCode = weatherData.current.weather_code;
var windSpeed = weatherData.current.wind_speed_10m;
var region = global.get('region') || 'London';

var hasThunderstorms = weatherCode >= 95;
var hasStrongWinds = windSpeed > 50;

// Check all combinations
if (hasThunderstorms && hasStrongWinds) {
    var windSpeedMph = Math.round(windSpeed * 0.621371 * 2) / 2;
    msg.payload = "Thunderstorms and strong winds forecast in the region around " + region + " (" + windSpeedMph + " mph). (Open-Meteo)";
    return msg;
} else if (hasThunderstorms) {
    msg.payload = "Thunderstorms forecast in the region around " + region + ". (Open-Meteo)";
    return msg;
} else if (hasStrongWinds) {
    var windSpeedMph = Math.round(windSpeed * 0.621371 * 2) / 2;
    msg.payload = "Strong winds forecast in the region around " + region + " (" + windSpeedMph + " mph). (Open-Meteo)";
    return msg;
}

// No severe weather detected
return null;

// Retrieve the processed count from flow context (initialize to 0 if not set)
let count = flow.get('processedCount') || 0; 

let numItems = flow.get('numItems') || 5;

// Process the message only if we haven't processed the required number of items yet
if (count < numItems) {
    count += 1;  // Increment the count for each processed item

    let messageContent = msg.payload;

    // Truncate the message if it's longer than 198 characters
    if (messageContent.length > 198) {
        messageContent = messageContent.slice(0, 198);  
    }

    msg.article = messageContent;

    // Update the processed count in flow context so it persists across messages
    flow.set('processedCount', count);

    return msg;
} else {
    return null;  // Stop processing further messages for this batch
}

// Get the long URL from msg.payload
let longUrl = msg.payload;

// Check if the long URL is valid
if (!longUrl || typeof longUrl !== 'string') {
    node.error("Invalid URL", msg);
    return null;  // Exit the function if the URL is invalid
}

// Check if the URL contains a '?'
let questionMarkIndex = longUrl.indexOf('?');

// If it contains a '?', remove everything after it, including the '?' itself
if (questionMarkIndex !== -1) {
    longUrl = longUrl.substring(0, questionMarkIndex);  // Keep the part before '?'
}

// Prepare the URL for TinyURL
let tinyUrlApi = `https://tinyurl.com/api-create.php?url=${encodeURIComponent(longUrl)}`;

// Set the HTTP request configuration
msg.url = tinyUrlApi;  // TinyURL API endpoint

return msg;

let inputString = msg.payload;

// Check if the string contains ",u" (case-insensitive)
let hasTinyUrl = inputString.toLowerCase().includes(',u');
flow.set('tinyurlFlag', hasTinyUrl ? 1 : 0);

// Just in case the message is wanted for other nodes...
return msg;

// Retrieve the article text (msg.article) and TinyURL (msg.payload)
let articleText = '- ' + msg.article;
let tinyUrl = msg.payload;

let maxLength = 196;

// Retrieve the flow context variable that indicates if we should append the TinyURL
let tinyurlFlag = flow.get('tinyurlFlag') || 0;  // Default to 0 if not set

// If tinyurlFlag is 1, append the TinyURL to the article text
if (tinyurlFlag === 1) {
    // Calculate remaining space for the article text after appending the TinyURL and a space
    let remainingSpace = maxLength - tinyUrl.length - 1;  // 1 for the space between TinyURL and article

    if (remainingSpace < articleText.length) {
        articleText = articleText.substring(0, remainingSpace);  // Truncate the article
    }

    // Combine the TinyURL and the article text
    msg.payload = articleText + ' ' + tinyUrl + '\n';
} else {
    // If tinyurlFlag is 0, just return the article text, truncated if necessary
    msg.payload = articleText.substring(0, maxLength) + '\n';
}

return msg;

// Parse input to set numItems
let inputString = msg.payload.trim();
let numItems = 5;  // Default numItems value

// Check if the string contains a comma followed by a number anywhere in the string
let regex = /,(\d+)/;
let match = inputString.match(regex);

if (match) {
    numItems = parseInt(match[1]);
    numItems = Math.min(numItems, 10);  // Limit numItems to 10
}

flow.set('numItems', numItems);

// Reset the processed count to 0 (start fresh for the new batch)
flow.set('processedCount', 0);

// Reset the 'alreadyProcessed' flag so that it doesn't block future messages
flow.set('alreadyProcessed', false);

// Store numItems in msg for later use
msg.numItems = numItems;
msg.payload = numItems;
return msg;

let quote = msg.payload[0].q;  // The quote text
let author = msg.payload[0].a; // The author

if (quote.trim().length === 0) {
        return null;
    }

msg.payload = 'Zen quote: ' + quote;
if (msg.payload.length > 198) {
        msg.payload = msg.payload.substring(0, 198); 
}   
return msg;

if ((global.get('info')) || (global.get('helpMsg'))) {
    msg.payload = (global.get('info') || '');
    return msg;
} else {
    msg.payload = 'MeshBop messaging service is online.'; // Default message
    return msg;
}

if (typeof msg.payload === 'string') {
    // Remove non-ASCII characters
    msg.payload = msg.payload.replace(/[^\x00-\x7F]/g, '');
    // Limit length to 198 characters
    msg.payload = msg.payload.slice(0, 198);
    // Trim whitespace and drop if empty
    if (msg.payload.trim() === '') {
        return null; // message is empty, do not send
    }
}

// Get the current local time in 24-hour format
let currentTime = new Date().toLocaleTimeString(global.get('locale') || 'en-GB', { hour12: false });

// Format the timestamp as DD-MMM HH:MM
let now = new Date();
let day = String(now.getDate()).padStart(2, '0');
let monthNames = ["Jan", "Feb", "Mar", "Apr", "May", "Jun",
    "Jul", "Aug", "Sep", "Oct", "Nov", "Dec"];
let month = monthNames[now.getMonth()];

// Extract HH:MM from currentTime (HH:MM:SS)
let hhmm = currentTime.split(':').slice(0, 2).join(':');

// Create second message with timestamp
let msgWithTimestamp = { ...msg };
msgWithTimestamp.payload = `${day}-${month} ${hhmm} ${msg.payload}`;

// Return both outputs: first is original, second is with timestamp
return [msg, msgWithTimestamp];

function generateRandomString() {
    const months = ["Jan", "Feb", "Mar", "Apr", "May", "Jun", "Jul", "Aug", "Sep", "Oct", "Nov", "Dec"];

    // Random day (01-31)
    const day = String(Math.floor(Math.random() * 31) + 1).padStart(2, '0');

    // Random month
    const month = months[Math.floor(Math.random() * months.length)];

    // Random year (1900-2099)
    const year = Math.floor(Math.random() * 200) + 1900;

    // Current local time in 24-hour format
    let currentTime = new Date().toLocaleTimeString(global.get('locale') || 'en-GB', { hour12: false });
    // Extract HH:MM
    let hhmm = currentTime.split(':').slice(0, 2).join(':');

    // Random length between 90 and 190
    const randomLength = Math.floor(Math.random() * (190 - 90 + 1)) + 90;

    // Generate random string of randomLength
    let randomText = '';
    while (randomText.length < randomLength) {
        randomText += Math.random().toString(36).substring(2);
    }
    randomText = randomText.substring(0, randomLength); // trim to exact length

    // Format: literal 'AAAA ' + date + HH:MM + ': ' + random text
    return `AAAA ${day}-${month}-${year} ${hhmm}: ${randomText}`;
}

msg.payload = generateRandomString();
return msg;

// Accumulate log lines in node context
let log = context.get('log') || [];

// Check for reset
if (msg.reset === true) {
    log = [];  // clear the log
} else if (msg.payload !== undefined) {
    let line = msg.payload;
    log.push(line);

    // keep last 20 lines (optional)
    if (log.length > 20) log.shift();
}

// store updated log in context
context.set('log', log);

// send the entire array to the template
return { payload: log };

// Get the current local time in 24-hour format
let currentTime = new Date().toLocaleTimeString(global.get('locale') || 'en-GB', { hour12: false });
// Extract HH:MM
let hhmm = currentTime.split(':').slice(0, 2).join(':');

// Get today's date
const now = new Date();
const day = String(now.getDate()).padStart(2, '0');
const monthNames = ["Jan", "Feb", "Mar", "Apr", "May", "Jun",
                    "Jul", "Aug", "Sep", "Oct", "Nov", "Dec"];
const month = monthNames[now.getMonth()];
const year = now.getFullYear();

// Split input at the first colon
let inboundID = "";
let messageText = "";
if (typeof msg.payload === "string") {
    const index = msg.payload.indexOf(':');
    if (index !== -1) {
        inboundID = msg.payload.substring(0, index).trim();   // ID before colon
        messageText = msg.payload.substring(index + 1).trim(); // Text after colon
    } else {
        inboundID = "ID";             // fallback if no colon
        messageText = msg.payload;
    }
}

// Construct final message
msg.payload = `${inboundID} ${day}-${month}-${year} ${hhmm}: ${messageText}`;

return msg;
